-- EBay CEO Donahoe Compensation Rises 81% to $29.7 Million in 2012
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   K u c e r a
-- 2013-03-18T21:22:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-18/ebay-ceo-donahoe-compensation-rises-81-to-29-7-million-in-2012.html
EBay Inc. Chief Executive Officer
 John Donahoe  received compensation of $29.7 million in 2012, an
increase of 81 percent from the previous year, the company said.  In addition to a base salary, Donahoe was also awarded cash
and stock under incentive plans, according to a filing with the
U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission today.  Donahoe was promoted to the top position in 2008.  To contact the reporter on this story:
